==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cottonseed oil
<hw>Cottonseed oil</hw>. <def>A fixed, semidrying oil extracted from
cottonseed. It is pale yellow when pure (sp. gr., .92-.93). and is
extensively used in soap making, in cookery, and as an adulterant of
other oils.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cotton State</ent>⟦br⟧
